## Summary

**ATO is beta-stage** (functional, some gaps). **Immediate blockers before production:**

1. **Division 7A benchmark rate** hardcoded for FY2024-25 — will fail July 2025 (fix: make dynamic)
2. **Entertainment deductibility** and **Instant Asset Write-Off threshold** not FY-aware — produces incorrect advice for historical analysis (add FY lookup)
3. **QuickBooks OAuth** untested end-to-end (test immediately)
4. **Multi-entity consolidation** is roadmap, not implemented (OK for MVP if single-org only)
5. **Rate stale-analysis detection** partially implemented (stamp on reports but not checked by engines)

**Architecture is sound** — multi-agent orchestration, RLS security, read-only design. **Tax law compliance is strong** except noted edge cases. **Data normalization is 80% done** (Xero/MYOB working, QuickBooks partial).

**Recommend**: Fix 1-3 above, then green-light beta launch with explicit "AI-generated estimates—requires professional review" warnings on all output.